Thomas Fennelly (b Moyne, County Tipperary 27 January 1845 - d Moycarkey 24 December 1927) was the Archbishop of the Roman Catholic Archdiocese of Cashel and Emly from 1902 until his retirement in 1913.Fennelly was educated at Thurles College; St Vincent’s, Castleknock; and St Patrick's College, Maynooth. He was ordained in 1870. He was parish priest of Moycarkey from 1889 until his appointment as Coadjutor Bishop of Cashel in 1901.
He succeeded Archbishop Croke on 22 July 1902.
